<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-07-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-07-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="816" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d816">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/12464.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Brazilian Minister</gloss> to
                                    Mexico<note n="49" xml:id="d816fn49">Representing the interests
                                    of the United States in Mexico; see “Severance of diplomatic
                                    relations between the United States and Mexico, etc.”</note> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Brazilian Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-07-10">
                                    <hi rend="italic">July 10, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>82. I beg to inform the Department that day before yesterday the protocol
                            signed at Niagara Falls<note n="50" xml:id="d816fn50">Protocol No. 4;
                                see <ref target="#pg_553">page 553</ref>. For the text of Protocol
                                No. 4, concluding the proposal of the Mediators, see <ref target="#pg_548">page 548</ref>.</note> was read before Congress
                            and that to-day Licenciado Francisco Carbajal, Chief Justice of the
                            Suprenn Court, was appointed Minister for Foreign Affairs and according
                            to reliable information he will become Provisional President.</p>
                        <p>For my guidance, and if agreeable to the Department, I should like to
                            learn its views in the event of the above-mentioned change.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Cardoso de Oliveira</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>